@startuml Blockchain Platform Comparison
!theme plain
title Comparative Analysis of Platforms for ITS
package "Hyperledger Fabric" as fabric {
    card "**Consensus Type**\nPBFT / RAFT" as fabric_consensus #lightblue
    card "**Transaction Rate**\nHigh (1000-3500 TPS)" as fabric_tps #lightgreen
    card "**Network Type**\nPrivate Consortium" as fabric_network
    card "**Privacy**\nPrivate Channels\nVery High" as fabric_privacy #lightgreen
    card "**Operating Cost**\nLow (no fees)" as fabric_cost #lightgreen
    card "**Scalability**\nModerate/High" as fabric_scale #yellow
    card "**ITS Suitability**\n★★★★★\nVery Suitable" as fabric_fit #lightgreen
}
package "Ethereum (PoA)" as ethereum {
    card "**Consensus Type**\nProof of Authority" as eth_consensus #lightblue
    card "**Transaction Rate**\nModerate (100-500 TPS)" as eth_tps #yellow
    card "**Network Type**\nPublic/Permissioned" as eth_network
    card "**Privacy**\nLow (public)\nModerate (private)" as eth_privacy #yellow
    card "**Operating Cost**\nModerate (gas)" as eth_cost #yellow
    card "**Scalability**\nModerate" as eth_scale #yellow
    card "**ITS Suitability**\n★★★☆☆\nModerate" as eth_fit #yellow
}
package "IOTA (Tangle/DAG)" as iota {
    card "**Consensus Type**\nTangle (DAG)" as iota_consensus #lightblue
    card "**Transaction Rate**\nVery High\n(1000+ TPS theoretical)" as iota_tps #lightgreen
    card "**Network Type**\nPublic Distributed" as iota_network
    card "**Privacy**\nLow (public)" as iota_privacy #red
    card "**Operating Cost**\nZero (no fees)" as iota_cost #lightgreen
    card "**Scalability**\nVery High" as iota_scale #lightgreen
    card "**ITS Suitability**\n★★★★☆\nHigh Potential" as iota_fit #yellow
}
fabric -[hidden]right-> ethereum
ethereum -[hidden]right-> iota
note bottom
    **Recommendation for ITS System:**
    **1st Choice: Hyperledger Fabric**
    ✓ Full control over participants
    ✓ Native privacy (channels)
    ✓ Adequate performance for ITS
    ✓ No transaction costs
    ✓ Enterprise maturity
    **2nd Choice: IOTA (for specific cases)**
    ✓ Scalability for M2M
    ✓ Microtransactions at no cost
    ✓ Suitable for frequent messages
    ⚠ Lower privacy
    ⚠ Lower maturity for consortiums
    **3rd Choice: Ethereum PoA**
    ⚠ Limited performance
    ⚠ Operational costs (gas)
    ✓ Mature ecosystem
    ✓ Available tooling
    **Weighted Criteria for ITS:**
    • Performance: 30%
    • Privacy: 25%
    • Control/Governance: 20%
    • Cost: 15%
    • Maturity: 10%
end note
@enduml
